text: The Pingualuit crater (; from Inuit "pimple"), is a relatively young impact crater. It is on the Ungava Peninsula in the region of Nord-du-Québec, in Quebec, Canada. The crater is in diameter, and is estimated to be 1.4 ± 0.1 million years old (Pleistocene). Earth Impact DB New Quebec The crater and the surrounding area are now part of Pingualuit National Park. The only species of fish in the crater lake is the Arctic char. The crater was formerly called the "Chubb Crater" and later the "New Quebec Crater" (). == References == Category:Craters Category:Geography of Quebec
